![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/27c662c2-71a7-461a-940a-f3c9a5f00347/ep249.jpg)

The Spidey Month Celebration is coming to a close and this is the last dance. Created by the Dynamic Duo of Jeph Loeb and Time Sale, Spider-Man: Blue is one of the most sentimental comics our friendly neighborhood wall-crawler has been in. It tells the story of how Gwen Stacey and Peter Parker fell in love, as Parker finds himself feeling "blue" on Valentine's Day. Full of heart, humor and heroics, Spider-Man: Blue is a quintessential story in the Spidey lore so join us as we recap and review Spider-Man Blue!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

  
